Only times Iï¿½ï¿½ï¿½ve been able to listen to podcasts is when Iï¿½ï¿½ï¿½m stuck in the car (only as a passenger, canï¿½ï¿½ï¿½t listen if Iï¿½ï¿½ï¿½m the one driving) or back when I worked for my aunt packaging first aide kits.I am a crochet advocate. So many free tutorials on YouTube and it was pretty easy for me to pick up. Once you know the basics and have made a few things itï¿½ï¿½ï¿½s pretty easy to think up your own simple designs too. For example one of my first projects was a cardigan that I made from a free pattern and it was so easy. It was rly just make a ton of squares and stitch them together. Now, I have never knit so I donï¿½ï¿½ï¿½t know if itï¿½ï¿½ï¿½s easier or more fun, but I can advocate for crocheting at least. Only thing is yarn has gotten pretty expensive, which is annoying :/Iï¿½ï¿½ï¿½ve heardality has gone down and prices have gone upIï¿½ï¿½ï¿½d really like to get into either knit or crochet but one of the reasons Iï¿½ï¿½ï¿½ve been hesitant (aside from the general feeling that starting a new hobby is super daunting) is that I donï¿½ï¿½ï¿½t know anything about yarn quality and Iï¿½ï¿½ï¿½m afraid of getting ripped off But I do think it would be really fun to have a hobby where I make something so I should buckle do

the nice thing is that if you have a craft store near you the yarn goes on sale from time to time. I kinda have clocked when my local craft stores do that and only buy sale yarn. Now online is a different matter, Iï¿½ï¿½ï¿½ve never bought yarn online so thatï¿½ï¿½ï¿½s like the wild West to meI would say if youï¿½ï¿½ï¿½re starting off, acrylic yarn is cheap even though it feels less nice. I would make your first projects in that and then maybe as you get better switch to other materials that might be slightly more expensive.Anyways. Definitely something to look into, Iï¿½ï¿½ï¿½m biased but I really think itï¿½ï¿½ï¿½s worth it. I struggle with feeling like Iï¿½ï¿½ï¿½m not doing enough if I sit down to listen to a podcast, but if Iï¿½ï¿½ï¿½m crocheting I feel immediately more productive.I will say, if youï¿½ï¿½ï¿½re into making clothes, making a crochet piece is often more expensive than say thrifting a piece. But if youï¿½ï¿½ï¿½re making something personalized that youï¿½ï¿½ï¿½ll wear often that wonï¿½ï¿½ï¿½t guse out of it and keep it way longer. Just some more disordered thoughts bc I love talking about hobbies. But anyway if you crochet or knit something you should definitely keep the mutuals posted and post a pic on here <3"

Only times Iï¿½ï¿½ï¿½ve been able to listen to podcasts is when Iï¿½ï¿½ï¿½m stuck in the car (only as a passenger, canï¿½ï¿½ï¿½t listen if Iï¿½ï¿½ï¿½m the one driving) or back when I worked for my aunt packaging first aide kits.I am a crochet advocate. So many free tutorials on YouTube and it was pretty easy for me to pick up. Once you know the basics and have made a few things itï¿½ï¿½ï¿½s pretty easy to think up your own simple designs too. For example one of my first projects was a cardigan that I made from a free pattern and it was so easy. It was rly just make a ton of squares and stitch them together. Now, I have never knit so I donï¿½ï¿½ï¿½t know if itï¿½ï¿½ï¿½s easier or more fun, but I can advocate for crocheting at least. Only thing is yarn has gotten pretty expensive, which is annoying :/Iï¿½ï¿½ï¿½ve heardality has gone down and prices have gone upIï¿½ï¿½ï¿½d really like to get into either knit or crochet but one of the reasons Iï¿½ï¿½ï¿½ve been hesitant (aside from the general feeling that starting a new hobby is super daunting) is that I donï¿½ï¿½ï¿½t know anything about yarn quality and Iï¿½ï¿½ï¿½m afraid of getting ripped off But I do think it would be really fun to have a hobby where I make something so I should buckle do

the nice thing is that if you have a craft store near you the yarn goes on sale from time to time. I kinda have clocked when my local craft stores do that and only buy sale yarn. Now online is a different matter, Iï¿½ï¿½ï¿½ve never bought yarn online so thatï¿½ï¿½ï¿½s like the wild West to meI would say if youï¿½ï¿½ï¿½re starting off, acrylic yarn is cheap even though it feels less nice. I would make your first projects in that and then maybe as you get better switch to other materials that might be slightly more expensive.Anyways. Definitely something to look into, Iï¿½ï¿½ï¿½m biased but I really think itï¿½ï¿½ï¿½s worth it. I struggle with feeling like Iï¿½ï¿½ï¿½m not doing enough if I sit down to listen to a podcast, but if Iï¿½ï¿½ï¿½m crocheting I feel immediately more productive.I will say, if youï¿½ï¿½ï¿½re into making clothes, making a crochet piece is often more expensive than say thrifting a piece. But if youï¿½ï¿½ï¿½re making something personalized that youï¿½ï¿½ï¿½ll wear often that wonï¿½ï¿½ï¿½t guse out of it and keep it way longer. Just some more disordered thoughts bc I love talking about hobbies. But anyway if you crochet or knit something you should definitely keep the mutuals posted and post a pic on here <3"

Only times Iï¿½ï¿½ï¿½ve been able to listen to podcasts is when Iï¿½ï¿½ï¿½m stuck in the car (only as a passenger, canï¿½ï¿½ï¿½t listen if Iï¿½ï¿½ï¿½m the one driving) or back when I worked for my aunt packaging first aide kits.I am a crochet advocate. So many free tutorials on YouTube and it was pretty easy for me to pick up. Once you know the basics and have made a few things itï¿½ï¿½ï¿½s pretty easy to think up your own simple designs too. For example one of my first projects was a cardigan that I made from a free pattern and it was so easy. It was rly just make a ton of squares and stitch them together. Now, I have never knit so I donï¿½ï¿½ï¿½t know if itï¿½ï¿½ï¿½s easier or more fun, but I can advocate for crocheting at least. Only thing is yarn has gotten pretty expensive, which is annoying :/Iï¿½ï¿½ï¿½ve heardality has gone down and prices have gone upIï¿½ï¿½ï¿½d really like to get into either knit or crochet but one of the reasons Iï¿½ï¿½ï¿½ve been hesitant (aside from the general feeling that starting a new hobby is super daunting) is that I donï¿½ï¿½ï¿½t know anything about yarn quality and Iï¿½ï¿½ï¿½m afraid of getting ripped off But I do think it would be really fun to have a hobby where I make something so I should buckle do

I would make your first projects in that and then maybe as you get better switch to other materials that might be slightly more expensive.Anyways. Definitely something to look into, Iï¿½ï¿½ï¿½m biased but I really think itï¿½ï¿½ï¿½s worth it. But if youï¿½ï¿½ï¿½re making something personalized that youï¿½ï¿½ï¿½ll wear often that wonï¿½ï¿½ï¿½t guse out of it and keep it way longer. Just some more disordered thoughts bc I love talking about hobbies. But anyway if you crochet or knit something you should definitely keep the mutuals posted and post a pic on here <3"

Only times Iï¿½ï¿½ï¿½ve been able to listen to podcasts is when Iï¿½ï¿½ï¿½m stuck in the car (only as a passenger, canï¿½ï¿½ï¿½t listen if Iï¿½ï¿½ï¿½m the one driving) or back when I worked for my aunt packaging first aide kits.I am a crochet advocate. So many free tutorials on YouTube and it was pretty easy for me to pick up. Once you know the basics and have made a few things itï¿½ï¿½ï¿½s pretty easy to think up your own simple designs too. For example one of my first projects was a cardigan that I made from a free pattern and it was so easy. It was rly just make a ton of squares and stitch them together. Now, I have never knit so I donï¿½ï¿½ï¿½t know if itï¿½ï¿½ï¿½s easier or more fun, but I can advocate for crocheting at least. Only thing is yarn has gotten pretty expensive, which is annoying :/Iï¿½ï¿½ï¿½ve heardality has gone down and prices have gone upIï¿½ï¿½ï¿½d really like to get into either knit or crochet but one of the reasons Iï¿½ï¿½ï¿½ve been hesitant (aside from the general feeling that starting a new hobby is super daunting) is that I donï¿½ï¿½ï¿½t know anything about yarn quality and Iï¿½ï¿½ï¿½m afraid of getting ripped off But I do think it would be really fun to have a hobby where I make something so I should buckle do

the nice thing is that if you have a craft store near you the yarn goes on sale from time to time. I kinda have clocked when my local craft stores do that and only buy sale yarn. Now online is a different matter, Iï¿½ï¿½ï¿½ve never bought yarn online so thatï¿½ï¿½ï¿½s like the wild West to meI would say if youï¿½ï¿½ï¿½re starting off, acrylic yarn is cheap even though it feels less nice. I would make your first projects in that and then maybe as you get better switch to other materials that might be slightly more expensive.Anyways. Definitely something to look into, Iï¿½ï¿½ï¿½m biased but I really think itï¿½ï¿½ï¿½s worth it. I struggle with feeling like Iï¿½ï¿½ï¿½m not doing enough if I sit down to listen to a podcast, but if Iï¿½ï¿½ï¿½m crocheting I feel immediately more productive.I will say, if youï¿½ï¿½ï¿½re into making clothes, making a crochet piece is often more expensive than say thrifting a piece. But if youï¿½ï¿½ï¿½re making something personalized that youï¿½ï¿½ï¿½ll wear often that wonï¿½ï¿½ï¿½t guse out of it and keep it way longer. Just some more disordered thoughts bc I love talking about hobbies. But anyway if you crochet or knit something you should definitely keep the mutuals posted and post a pic on here <3"

Blog: redglassbird,2024-04-11 15:34:47,https://www.tumblr.com/blog/view/redglassbird/747477074164482048,,"gallium-spoon:redglassbird:gallium-spoon:I need to take up knitting or jewelry making or something so I can listen to podcasts I gotta have something to do with my hands or I canï¿½ï¿½ï¿½t focus. Only times Iï¿½ï¿½ï¿½ve been able to listen to podcasts is when Iï¿½ï¿½ï¿½m stuck in the car (only as a passenger, canï¿½ï¿½ï¿½t listen if Iï¿½ï¿½ï¿½m the one driving) or back when I worked for my aunt packaging first aide kits.I am a crochet advocate. So many free tutorials on YouTube and it was pretty easy for me to pick up. Once you know the basics and have made a few things itï¿½ï¿½ï¿½s pretty easy to think up your own simple designs too. For example one of my first projects was a cardigan that I made from a free pattern and it was so easy. It was rly just make a ton of squares and stitch them together. Now, I have never knit so I donï¿½ï¿½ï¿½t know if itï¿½ï¿½ï¿½s easier or more fun, but I can advocate for crocheting at least. Only thing is yarn has gotten pretty expensive, which is annoying :/Iï¿½ï¿½ï¿½ve heardality has gone down and prices have gone upIï¿½ï¿½ï¿½d really like to get into either knit or crochet but one of the reasons Iï¿½ï¿½ï¿½ve been hesitant (aside from the general feeling that starting a new hobby is super daunting) is that I donï¿½ï¿½ï¿½t know anything about yarn quality and Iï¿½ï¿½ï¿½m afraid of getting ripped off But I do think it would be really fun to have a hobby where I make something so I should buckle do

the nice thing is that if you have a craft store near you the yarn goes on sale from time to time. I kinda have clocked when my local craft stores do that and only buy sale yarn. Now online is a different matter, Iï¿½ï¿½ï¿½ve never bought yarn online so thatï¿½ï¿½ï¿½s like the wild West to meI would say if youï¿½ï¿½ï¿½re starting off, acrylic yarn is cheap even though it feels less nice. I would make your first projects in that and then maybe as you get better switch to other materials that might be slightly more expensive.Anyways. Definitely something to look into, Iï¿½ï¿½ï¿½m biased but I really think itï¿½ï¿½ï¿½s worth it. I struggle with feeling like Iï¿½ï¿½ï¿½m not doing enough if I sit down to listen to a podcast, but if Iï¿½ï¿½ï¿½m crocheting I feel immediately more productive.I will say, if youï¿½ï¿½ï¿½re into making clothes, making a crochet piece is often more expensive than say thrifting a piece. But if youï¿½ï¿½ï¿½re making something personalized that youï¿½ï¿½ï¿½ll wear often that wonï¿½ï¿½ï¿½t guse out of it and keep it way longer. Just some more disordered thoughts bc I love talking about hobbies. But anyway if you crochet or knit something you should definitely keep the mutuals posted and post a pic on here <3"

Only thing is yarn has gotten pretty expensive, which is annoying :/Iï¿½ï¿½ï¿½ve heardality has gone down and prices have gone upIï¿½ï¿½ï¿½d really like to get into either knit or crochet but one of the reasons Iï¿½ï¿½ï¿½ve been hesitant (aside from the general feeling that starting a new hobby is super daunting) is that I donï¿½ï¿½ï¿½t know anything about yarn quality and Iï¿½ï¿½ï¿½m afraid of getting ripped off But I do think it would be really fun to have a hobby where I make something so I should buckle do

the nice thing is that if you have a craft store near you the yarn goes on sale from time to time. I kinda have clocked when my local craft stores do that and only buy sale yarn. Now online is a different matter, Iï¿½ï¿½ï¿½ve never bought yarn online so thatï¿½ï¿½ï¿½s like the wild West to meI would say if youï¿½ï¿½ï¿½re starting off, acrylic yarn is cheap even though it feels less nice. I would make your first projects in that and then maybe as you get better switch to other materials that might be slightly more expensive.Anyways. Definitely something to look into, Iï¿½ï¿½ï¿½m biased but I really think itï¿½ï¿½ï¿½s worth it. I struggle with feeling like Iï¿½ï¿½ï¿½m not doing enough if I sit down to listen to a podcast, but if Iï¿½ï¿½ï¿½m crocheting I feel immediately more productive.I will say, if youï¿½ï¿½ï¿½re into making clothes, making a crochet piece is often more expensive than say thrifting a piece. But if youï¿½ï¿½ï¿½re making something personalized that youï¿½ï¿½ï¿½ll wear often that wonï¿½ï¿½ï¿½t guse out of it and keep it way longer. Just some more disordered thoughts bc I love talking about hobbies. But anyway if you crochet or knit something you should definitely keep the mutuals posted and post a pic on here <3"

Only times Iï¿½ï¿½ï¿½ve been able to listen to podcasts is when Iï¿½ï¿½ï¿½m stuck in the car (only as a passenger, canï¿½ï¿½ï¿½t listen if Iï¿½ï¿½ï¿½m the one driving) or back when I worked for my aunt packaging first aide kits.I am a crochet advocate. So many free tutorials on YouTube and it was pretty easy for me to pick up. Once you know the basics and have made a few things itï¿½ï¿½ï¿½s pretty easy to think up your own simple designs too. For example one of my first projects was a cardigan that I made from a free pattern and it was so easy. It was rly just make a ton of squares and stitch them together. Now, I have never knit so I donï¿½ï¿½ï¿½t know if itï¿½ï¿½ï¿½s easier or more fun, but I can advocate for crocheting at least. Only thing is yarn has gotten pretty expensive, which is annoying :/Iï¿½ï¿½ï¿½ve heardality has gone down and prices have gone upIï¿½ï¿½ï¿½d really like to get into either knit or crochet but one of the reasons Iï¿½ï¿½ï¿½ve been hesitant (aside from the general feeling that starting a new hobby is super daunting) is that I donï¿½ï¿½ï¿½t know anything about yarn quality and Iï¿½ï¿½ï¿½m afraid of getting ripped off But I do think it would be really fun to have a hobby where I make something so I should buckle do

the nice thing is that if you have a craft store near you the yarn goes on sale from time to time. I kinda have clocked when my local craft stores do that and only buy sale yarn. Now online is a different matter, Iï¿½ï¿½ï¿½ve never bought yarn online so thatï¿½ï¿½ï¿½s like the wild West to meI would say if youï¿½ï¿½ï¿½re starting off, acrylic yarn is cheap even though it feels less nice. I would make your first projects in that and then maybe as you get better switch to other materials that might be slightly more expensive.Anyways. Definitely something to look into, Iï¿½ï¿½ï¿½m biased but I really think itï¿½ï¿½ï¿½s worth it. I struggle with feeling like Iï¿½ï¿½ï¿½m not doing enough if I sit down to listen to a podcast, but if Iï¿½ï¿½ï¿½m crocheting I feel immediately more productive.I will say, if youï¿½ï¿½ï¿½re into making clothes, making a crochet piece is often more expensive than say thrifting a piece. But if youï¿½ï¿½ï¿½re making something personalized that youï¿½ï¿½ï¿½ll wear often that wonï¿½ï¿½ï¿½t guse out of it and keep it way longer. Just some more disordered thoughts bc I love talking about hobbies. But anyway if you crochet or knit something you should definitely keep the mutuals posted and post a pic on here <3"

Only times Iï¿½ï¿½ï¿½ve been able to listen to podcasts is when Iï¿½ï¿½ï¿½m stuck in the car (only as a passenger, canï¿½ï¿½ï¿½t listen if Iï¿½ï¿½ï¿½m the one driving) or back when I worked for my aunt packaging first aide kits.I am a crochet advocate. So many free tutorials on YouTube and it was pretty easy for me to pick up. Once you know the basics and have made a few things itï¿½ï¿½ï¿½s pretty easy to think up your own simple designs too. For example one of my first projects was a cardigan that I made from a free pattern and it was so easy. It was rly just make a ton of squares and stitch them together. Now, I have never knit so I donï¿½ï¿½ï¿½t know if itï¿½ï¿½ï¿½s easier or more fun, but I can advocate for crocheting at least. Only thing is yarn has gotten pretty expensive, which is annoying :/Iï¿½ï¿½ï¿½ve heardality has gone down and prices have gone upIï¿½ï¿½ï¿½d really like to get into either knit or crochet but one of the reasons Iï¿½ï¿½ï¿½ve been hesitant (aside from the general feeling that starting a new hobby is super daunting) is that I donï¿½ï¿½ï¿½t know anything about yarn quality and Iï¿½ï¿½ï¿½m afraid of getting ripped off But I do think it would be really fun to have a hobby where I make something so I should buckle do

the nice thing is that if you have a craft store near you the yarn goes on sale from time to time. I kinda have clocked when my local craft stores do that and only buy sale yarn. Now online is a different matter, Iï¿½ï¿½ï¿½ve never bought yarn online so thatï¿½ï¿½ï¿½s like the wild West to meI would say if youï¿½ï¿½ï¿½re starting off, acrylic yarn is cheap even though it feels less nice. I would make your first projects in that and then maybe as you get better switch to other materials that might be slightly more expensive.Anyways. Definitely something to look into, Iï¿½ï¿½ï¿½m biased but I really think itï¿½ï¿½ï¿½s worth it. I struggle with feeling like Iï¿½ï¿½ï¿½m not doing enough if I sit down to listen to a podcast, but if Iï¿½ï¿½ï¿½m crocheting I feel immediately more productive.I will say, if youï¿½ï¿½ï¿½re into making clothes, making a crochet piece is often more expensive than say thrifting a piece. But if youï¿½ï¿½ï¿½re making something personalized that youï¿½ï¿½ï¿½ll wear often that wonï¿½ï¿½ï¿½t guse out of it and keep it way longer. Just some more disordered thoughts bc I love talking about hobbies. But anyway if you crochet or knit something you should definitely keep the mutuals posted and post a pic on here <3"

Only times Iï¿½ï¿½ï¿½ve been able to listen to podcasts is when Iï¿½ï¿½ï¿½m stuck in the car (only as a passenger, canï¿½ï¿½ï¿½t listen if Iï¿½ï¿½ï¿½m the one driving) or back when I worked for my aunt packaging first aide kits.I am a crochet advocate. So many free tutorials on YouTube and it was pretty easy for me to pick up. Once you know the basics and have made a few things itï¿½ï¿½ï¿½s pretty easy to think up your own simple designs too. For example one of my first projects was a cardigan that I made from a free pattern and it was so easy. It was rly just make a ton of squares and stitch them together. Now, I have never knit so I donï¿½ï¿½ï¿½t know if itï¿½ï¿½ï¿½s easier or more fun, but I can advocate for crocheting at least. Only thing is yarn has gotten pretty expensive, which is annoying :/Iï¿½ï¿½ï¿½ve heardality has gone down and prices have gone upIï¿½ï¿½ï¿½d really like to get into either knit or crochet but one of the reasons Iï¿½ï¿½ï¿½ve been hesitant (aside from the general feeling that starting a new hobby is super daunting) is that I donï¿½ï¿½ï¿½t know anything about yarn quality and Iï¿½ï¿½ï¿½m afraid of getting ripped off But I do think it would be really fun to have a hobby where I make something so I should buckle do

the nice thing is that if you have a craft store near you the yarn goes on sale from time to time. I kinda have clocked when my local craft stores do that and only buy sale yarn. Now online is a different matter, Iï¿½ï¿½ï¿½ve never bought yarn online so thatï¿½ï¿½ï¿½s like the wild West to meI would say if youï¿½ï¿½ï¿½re starting off, acrylic yarn is cheap even though it feels less nice. I would make your first projects in that and then maybe as you get better switch to other materials that might be slightly more expensive.Anyways. Definitely something to look into, Iï¿½ï¿½ï¿½m biased but I really think itï¿½ï¿½ï¿½s worth it. I struggle with feeling like Iï¿½ï¿½ï¿½m not doing enough if I sit down to listen to a podcast, but if Iï¿½ï¿½ï¿½m crocheting I feel immediately more productive.I will say, if youï¿½ï¿½ï¿½re into making clothes, making a crochet piece is often more expensive than say thrifting a piece. But if youï¿½ï¿½ï¿½re making something personalized that youï¿½ï¿½ï¿½ll wear often that wonï¿½ï¿½ï¿½t guse out of it and keep it way longer. Just some more disordered thoughts bc I love talking about hobbies. But anyway if you crochet or knit something you should definitely keep the mutuals posted and post a pic on here <3"

Only times Iï¿½ï¿½ï¿½ve been able to listen to podcasts is when Iï¿½ï¿½ï¿½m stuck in the car (only as a passenger, canï¿½ï¿½ï¿½t listen if Iï¿½ï¿½ï¿½m the one driving) or back when I worked for my aunt packaging first aide kits.I am a crochet advocate. So many free tutorials on YouTube and it was pretty easy for me to pick up. Once you know the basics and have made a few things itï¿½ï¿½ï¿½s pretty easy to think up your own simple designs too. For example one of my first projects was a cardigan that I made from a free pattern and it was so easy. It was rly just make a ton of squares and stitch them together. Now, I have never knit so I donï¿½ï¿½ï¿½t know if itï¿½ï¿½ï¿½s easier or more fun, but I can advocate for crocheting at least. Only thing is yarn has gotten pretty expensive, which is annoying :/Iï¿½ï¿½ï¿½ve heardality has gone down and prices have gone upIï¿½ï¿½ï¿½d really like to get into either knit or crochet but one of the reasons Iï¿½ï¿½ï¿½ve been hesitant (aside from the general feeling that starting a new hobby is super daunting) is that I donï¿½ï¿½ï¿½t know anything about yarn quality and Iï¿½ï¿½ï¿½m afraid of getting ripped off But I do think it would be really fun to have a hobby where I make something so I should buckle do

I would make your first projects in that and then maybe as you get better switch to other materials that might be slightly more expensive.Anyways. Definitely something to look into, Iï¿½ï¿½ï¿½m biased but I really think itï¿½ï¿½ï¿½s worth it. But if youï¿½ï¿½ï¿½re making something personalized that youï¿½ï¿½ï¿½ll wear often that wonï¿½ï¿½ï¿½t guse out of it and keep it way longer. Just some more disordered thoughts bc I love talking about hobbies. But anyway if you crochet or knit something you should definitely keep the mutuals posted and post a pic on here <3"

Only times Iï¿½ï¿½ï¿½ve been able to listen to podcasts is when Iï¿½ï¿½ï¿½m stuck in the car (only as a passenger, canï¿½ï¿½ï¿½t listen if Iï¿½ï¿½ï¿½m the one driving) or back when I worked for my aunt packaging first aide kits.I am a crochet advocate. So many free tutorials on YouTube and it was pretty easy for me to pick up. Once you know the basics and have made a few things itï¿½ï¿½ï¿½s pretty easy to think up your own simple designs too. For example one of my first projects was a cardigan that I made from a free pattern and it was so easy. It was rly just make a ton of squares and stitch them together. Now, I have never knit so I donï¿½ï¿½ï¿½t know if itï¿½ï¿½ï¿½s easier or more fun, but I can advocate for crocheting at least. Only thing is yarn has gotten pretty expensive, which is annoying :/Iï¿½ï¿½ï¿½ve heardality has gone down and prices have gone upIï¿½ï¿½ï¿½d really like to get into either knit or crochet but one of the reasons Iï¿½ï¿½ï¿½ve been hesitant (aside from the general feeling that starting a new hobby is super daunting) is that I donï¿½ï¿½ï¿½t know anything about yarn quality and Iï¿½ï¿½ï¿½m afraid of getting ripped off But I do think it would be really fun to have a hobby where I make something so I should buckle do

the nice thing is that if you have a craft store near you the yarn goes on sale from time to time. I kinda have clocked when my local craft stores do that and only buy sale yarn. Now online is a different matter, Iï¿½ï¿½ï¿½ve never bought yarn online so thatï¿½ï¿½ï¿½s like the wild West to meI would say if youï¿½ï¿½ï¿½re starting off, acrylic yarn is cheap even though it feels less nice. I would make your first projects in that and then maybe as you get better switch to other materials that might be slightly more expensive.Anyways. Definitely something to look into, Iï¿½ï¿½ï¿½m biased but I really think itï¿½ï¿½ï¿½s worth it. I struggle with feeling like Iï¿½ï¿½ï¿½m not doing enough if I sit down to listen to a podcast, but if Iï¿½ï¿½ï¿½m crocheting I feel immediately more productive.I will say, if youï¿½ï¿½ï¿½re into making clothes, making a crochet piece is often more expensive than say thrifting a piece. But if youï¿½ï¿½ï¿½re making something personalized that youï¿½ï¿½ï¿½ll wear often that wonï¿½ï¿½ï¿½t guse out of it and keep it way longer. Just some more disordered thoughts bc I love talking about hobbies. But anyway if you crochet or knit something you should definitely keep the mutuals posted and post a pic on here <3"

Blog: redglassbird,2024-04-11 15:34:47,https://www.tumblr.com/blog/view/redglassbird/747477074164482048,,"gallium-spoon:redglassbird:gallium-spoon:I need to take up knitting or jewelry making or something so I can listen to podcasts I gotta have something to do with my hands or I canï¿½ï¿½ï¿½t focus. Only times Iï¿½ï¿½ï¿½ve been able to listen to podcasts is when Iï¿½ï¿½ï¿½m stuck in the car (only as a passenger, canï¿½ï¿½ï¿½t listen if Iï¿½ï¿½ï¿½m the one driving) or back when I worked for my aunt packaging first aide kits.I am a crochet advocate. So many free tutorials on YouTube and it was pretty easy for me to pick up. Once you know the basics and have made a few things itï¿½ï¿½ï¿½s pretty easy to think up your own simple designs too. For example one of my first projects was a cardigan that I made from a free pattern and it was so easy. It was rly just make a ton of squares and stitch them together. Now, I have never knit so I donï¿½ï¿½ï¿½t know if itï¿½ï¿½ï¿½s easier or more fun, but I can advocate for crocheting at least. Only thing is yarn has gotten pretty expensive, which is annoying :/Iï¿½ï¿½ï¿½ve heardality has gone down and prices have gone upIï¿½ï¿½ï¿½d really like to get into either knit or crochet but one of the reasons Iï¿½ï¿½ï¿½ve been hesitant (aside from the general feeling that starting a new hobby is super daunting) is that I donï¿½ï¿½ï¿½t know anything about yarn quality and Iï¿½ï¿½ï¿½m afraid of getting ripped off But I do think it would be really fun to have a hobby where I make something so I should buckle do

the nice thing is that if you have a craft store near you the yarn goes on sale from time to time. I kinda have clocked when my local craft stores do that and only buy sale yarn. Now online is a different matter, Iï¿½ï¿½ï¿½ve never bought yarn online so thatï¿½ï¿½ï¿½s like the wild West to meI would say if youï¿½ï¿½ï¿½re starting off, acrylic yarn is cheap even though it feels less nice. I would make your first projects in that and then maybe as you get better switch to other materials that might be slightly more expensive.Anyways. Definitely something to look into, Iï¿½ï¿½ï¿½m biased but I really think itï¿½ï¿½ï¿½s worth it. I struggle with feeling like Iï¿½ï¿½ï¿½m not doing enough if I sit down to listen to a podcast, but if Iï¿½ï¿½ï¿½m crocheting I feel immediately more productive.I will say, if youï¿½ï¿½ï¿½re into making clothes, making a crochet piece is often more expensive than say thrifting a piece. But if youï¿½ï¿½ï¿½re making something personalized that youï¿½ï¿½ï¿½ll wear often that wonï¿½ï¿½ï¿½t guse out of it and keep it way longer. Just some more disordered thoughts bc I love talking about hobbies. But anyway if you crochet or knit something you should definitely keep the mutuals posted and post a pic on here <3"

Only thing is yarn has gotten pretty expensive, which is annoying :/Iï¿½ï¿½ï¿½ve heardality has gone down and prices have gone upIï¿½ï¿½ï¿½d really like to get into either knit or crochet but one of the reasons Iï¿½ï¿½ï¿½ve been hesitant (aside from the general feeling that starting a new hobby is super daunting) is that I donï¿½ï¿½ï¿½t know anything about yarn quality and Iï¿½ï¿½ï¿½m afraid of getting ripped off But I do think it would be really fun to have a hobby where I make something so I should buckle do

the nice thing is that if you have a craft store near you the yarn goes on sale from time to time. I kinda have clocked when my local craft stores do that and only buy sale yarn. Now online is a different matter, Iï¿½ï¿½ï¿½ve never bought yarn online so thatï¿½ï¿½ï¿½s like the wild West to meI would say if youï¿½ï¿½ï¿½re starting off, acrylic yarn is cheap even though it feels less nice. I would make your first projects in that and then maybe as you get better switch to other materials that might be slightly more expensive.Anyways. Definitely something to look into, Iï¿½ï¿½ï¿½m biased but I really think itï¿½ï¿½ï¿½s worth it. I struggle with feeling like Iï¿½ï¿½ï¿½m not doing enough if I sit down to listen to a podcast, but if Iï¿½ï¿½ï¿½m crocheting I feel immediately more productive.I will say, if youï¿½ï¿½ï¿½re into making clothes, making a crochet piece is often more expensive than say thrifting a piece. But if youï¿½ï¿½ï¿½re making something personalized that youï¿½ï¿½ï¿½ll wear often that wonï¿½ï¿½ï¿½t guse out of it and keep it way longer. Just some more disordered thoughts bc I love talking about hobbies. But anyway if you crochet or knit something you should definitely keep the mutuals posted and post a pic on here <3"

Only times Iï¿½ï¿½ï¿½ve been able to listen to podcasts is when Iï¿½ï¿½ï¿½m stuck in the car (only as a passenger, canï¿½ï¿½ï¿½t listen if Iï¿½ï¿½ï¿½m the one driving) or back when I worked for my aunt packaging first aide kits.I am a crochet advocate. So many free tutorials on YouTube and it was pretty easy for me to pick up. Once you know the basics and have made a few things itï¿½ï¿½ï¿½s pretty easy to think up your own simple designs too. For example one of my first projects was a cardigan that I made from a free pattern and it was so easy. It was rly just make a ton of squares and stitch them together. Now, I have never knit so I donï¿½ï¿½ï¿½t know if itï¿½ï¿½ï¿½s easier or more fun, but I can advocate for crocheting at least. Only thing is yarn has gotten pretty expensive, which is annoying :/Iï¿½ï¿½ï¿½ve heardality has gone down and prices have gone upIï¿½ï¿½ï¿½d really like to get into either knit or crochet but one of the reasons Iï¿½ï¿½ï¿½ve been hesitant (aside from the general feeling that starting a new hobby is super daunting) is that I donï¿½ï¿½ï¿½t know anything about yarn quality and Iï¿½ï¿½ï¿½m afraid of getting ripped off But I do think it would be really fun to have a hobby where I make something so I should buckle do

the nice thing is that if you have a craft store near you the yarn goes on sale from time to time. I kinda have clocked when my local craft stores do that and only buy sale yarn. Now online is a different matter, Iï¿½ï¿½ï¿½ve never bought yarn online so thatï¿½ï¿½ï¿½s like the wild West to meI would say if youï¿½ï¿½ï¿½re starting off, acrylic yarn is cheap even though it feels less nice. I would make your first projects in that and then maybe as you get better switch to other materials that might be slightly more expensive.Anyways. Definitely something to look into, Iï¿½ï¿½ï¿½m biased but I really think itï¿½ï¿½ï¿½s worth it. I struggle with feeling like Iï¿½ï¿½ï¿½m not doing enough if I sit down to listen to a podcast, but if Iï¿½ï¿½ï¿½m crocheting I feel immediately more productive.I will say, if youï¿½ï¿½ï¿½re into making clothes, making a crochet piece is often more expensive than say thrifting a piece. But if youï¿½ï¿½ï¿½re making something personalized that youï¿½ï¿½ï¿½ll wear often that wonï¿½ï¿½ï¿½t guse out of it and keep it way longer. Just some more disordered thoughts bc I love talking about hobbies. But anyway if you crochet or knit something you should definitely keep the mutuals posted and post a pic on here <3"
